        <div class="prose-dark">
          <h2>What Is an Answer Engine?</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>An answer engine is any system that delivers a direct, synthesised response to a user query rather than a list of sources to investigate.</strong>
            The distinction is fundamental: a search engine returns a ranked set of results; an answer engine returns an answer.
          </p>
          <p>
            The major answer engine surfaces brands must optimise for today are:
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line)]">
                <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--accent)]">Platform</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--accent)]">Answer Format</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--accent)]">Mechanism</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-ink-300">
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">Google Featured Snippets</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Paragraph, list, or table extracted from a single page</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Passage extraction from ranked organic results</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">Google AI Overviews</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Synthesised paragraph with cited sources</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Generative AI + live web retrieval</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">People Also Ask</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Expandable answer boxes triggered by related queries</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Passage extraction, often from different pages</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">Perplexity</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Synthesised answer with numbered source citations</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">RAG (retrieval-augmented generation)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">Microsoft Copilot</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Conversational answer with inline citations</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">LLM + Bing web retrieval</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--line-soft)]">
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">ChatGPT (with browsing)</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Conversational answer citing retrieved pages</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">LLM + selective web retrieval</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-ink-100">Voice Assistants (Siri, Alexa, Google)</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Single spoken answer — no link list</td>
                <td class="px-5 py-3">Featured snippet selection or knowledge graph</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
